snippet.textDisplay: For people who are fighting for the origin of this song, please understand when this song was written it was only Bengal Presidency. Now what is Bengal Presidency in details you can Google it but West Bengal, Bangladesh & Assam was very much one state at that point of time. Now, Sundori Kamola is a Bhawaiya Song, which is a popular folk music in Rangpur District of Bangladesh. This form of music is also populer in Cooch Bihar, Jalpaiguri, part of Darjeeling in West Bangal and Goalpara of Assam. So, this song itself is a mix of so many cultures of India. So stop abusing each other. Also guys, Bengali & Assamese has the same origin. What difference does it make weather it's Bengali or Assamese???? It's a beautiful song describing a village woman and her emotions, why can't we just appreciate????
